  "text": "The Kubernetes API server authentication chain is constructed in pkg/kubeapiserver/authenticator/config.go in the New() function (lines 98-236). This is the central orchestrator that builds the complete authentication mechanism.\n\nThe chain construction process follows this order:\n\n1. **Front-proxy/Request Header Authenticator** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/headerrequest/requestheader.go, NewDynamicVerifyOptionsSecure at line 115): Handles client certificate verification from front proxies and extracts user identity from request headers. Used when RequestHeaderConfig is provided.\n\n2. **Client Certificate Authenticator (X.509)** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/x509/x509.go, NewDynamic at line 129): Verifies client certificates from mutual TLS connections and extracts user information from the certificate chain using CommonNameUserConversion.\n\n3. **Bearer Token Authenticators** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/bearertoken/bearertoken.go, New at line 36): Processes bearer tokens from Authorization headers. Multiple token authenticators are composed internally:\n   - Token file authenticator (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/token/tokenfile/tokenfile.go)\n   - Service Account token authenticator (pkg/serviceaccount/jwt.go, JWTTokenAuthenticator at line 227): Authenticates Kubernetes service account tokens using JWT validation with public key verification\n   - Bootstrap token authenticator\n   - OpenID Connect/JWT authenticators\n   - Webhook token authenticator\n\nThese token authenticators are combined using token union (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/token/union/union.go) at line 193 in config.go, then wrapped with optional caching. Token authentication results are then passed through the bearer token request authenticator and websocket protocol authenticator (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/websocket/protocol.go, NewProtocolAuthenticator at line 44).\n\n4. **Union/Chain** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/union/union.go, New at line 36): Combines all request authenticators into a single chain that tries each authenticator in order until one succeeds.\n\n5. **Authenticated Group Adder** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/group/authenticated_group_adder.go, NewAuthenticatedGroupAdder at line 35): Adds the system:authenticated group to successfully authenticated users.\n\n6. **Anonymous Authenticator** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/anonymous/anonymous.go, NewAuthenticator at line 55): Falls back to anonymous authentication for any request that doesn't match other authenticators, when anonymous authentication is enabled.\n\nThe delegating authenticator factory (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/authenticatorfactory/delegating.go) provides an alternative factory for building delegating authenticators used by other components like the kubelet."
